AgriConnect Project Guide & Developer Handbook ðŸ“˜
Yeh guide aapko poore project ka structure samjhne aur aage ke features khud bina confusion ke implement karne mein madad karegi.

1. Backend Structure (Server) âš™ï¸
Location: server/src/

Ab humne logic ko Roles ke hisaab se divide kar diya hai. Monolithic code nahi hai.

ðŸ“‚ Controllers (server/src/controllers/)
Yahan aapka main "business logic" rahega.

farmerController.js: ðŸšœ Sirf Farmer ka logic.
Example: New Crop add karna, Farmer Profile update, Farm details.
Future Work: Agar "Sell Product" feature banana hai, toh code yahan likhein.
vendorController.js: ðŸª Sirf Vendor ka logic.
Example: Orders dekhna, Bulk buying request, Vendor Profile.
customerController.js: ðŸ›’ Sirf Customer ka logic.
Example: Cart management, Buying vegetables, Address updates.
userController.js: ðŸ” Common Logic (Sabke liye same).
Isme sirf Login, OTP, Password Reset, aur Common Profile Fetch (getProfile) ka code hai. Isme role-specific logic mat likhna.
ðŸ“‚ Routes (server/src/routes/)
Yahan API endpoints define hote hain jo Controllers ko call karte hain.

farmerRoutes.js: Endpoints start with /api/farmers/...
vendorRoutes.js: Endpoints start with /api/vendors/...
customerRoutes.js: Endpoints start with /api/customers/...
UserRoutes.js: Endpoints start with /api/auth/... (Login/OTP).
ðŸ“‚ Models (server/src/models/)
Database schemas.

User.js: Base info (Name, Email, Mobile, Password, Role). Sab users ke paas ye hota hai.
Farmer.js: Linked to User. Contains farmSize, crops, etc.
Vendor.js: Linked to User. Contains shopName, capacity, etc.
Customer.js: Linked to User. Contains preferences, cart, etc.
2. Frontend Structure (Client) ðŸŽ¨
Location: client/src/

Frontend bhi roles ke hisaab se sorted hai.

ðŸ“‚ Components by Role
src/components/Farmers/: Saare Farmer pages yahan hain (Dashboard, Registration, Product List).
src/components/Vendors/: Vendor pages (Registration, Market View).
src/components/Customers/: Customer pages (Shopping, Cart).
ðŸ“‚ API Calls (client/src/api/)
axios.js: Base configuration settings.
userApi.js: Yahan saare API functions likhein.
Tip: Aap chaho toh farmerApi.js, vendorApi.js alag bana sakte ho clarity ke liye.
3. How To Implement New Features (Step-by-Step) ðŸ› ï¸
Agar aapko ek naya feature banana hai, man lijiye "Farmer Add Product", toh ye steps follow karein:

Step 1: Backend Controller
File: server/src/controllers/farmerController.js

export const addProduct = async (req, res) => {
    // Logic to save product in DB
    // req.user.id se farmer pata chalega
};
Step 2: Backend Route
File: server/src/routes/farmerRoutes.js

import { addProduct } from '../controllers/farmerController.js';
// Route banayein
router.post('/add-product', auth('farmer'), addProduct);
(Ab aapka API endpoint ban gaya: POST /api/farmers/add-product)

Step 3: Frontend API Function
File: client/src/api/userApi.js (ya new farmerApi.js)

export const addProductApi = async (productData) => {
    const response = await api.post('/farmers/add-product', productData);
    return response.data;
};
Step 4: Frontend UI
File: client/src/components/Farmers/AddProduct.jsx

Form banayein.
addProductApi function call karein button click par.
4. Key Things to Remember ðŸ’¡
Auth Middleware: Backend routes mein auth('farmer') ya auth('vendor') zaroor lagayein taaki galat user access na kar sake.
Common vs Specific:
Login/OTP related kuch bhi ho -> userController.js / /api/auth
Business related kuch bhi ho -> Role specific controller / /api/role
Refactoring is Done: Ab aapka code clean hai. Purani monolithic approach use mat karna.
Good luck implementing new features! ðŸš€

